Deploy it.

For interviews, your story becomes very strong:

"I built an AI-powered code review assistant. The iOS app allows developers to upload code or connect repositories. The backend processes the code, performs static analysis, retrieves relevant project context using embeddings, and uses an LLM to generate structured review feedback."

That is a much stronger story than:

"I trained a model on a dataset and got 92% accuracy."

One adjustment I would make: don't spend 4–6 months only learning ML algorithms before building. Your existing SwiftUI + Flask skills are valuable. Learn the required ML/AI concepts while building the project.

Your fastest path is:

SwiftUI + Flask (already have) → ML fundamentals → LLM/RAG → AI product.
